place.name: COLKIRK
place.gazetteerText: COLKIRK, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; near the Norfolk railway and the river Wensum, 2 miles S of Fakenham. Post town, Fakenham. Acres, 1, 482. Real property, £2, 824. Pop., 473. Houses, 97. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory, united with the rectory of Stibbard, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £788.* Patron, Henry Hoare, Esq. The church was repaired in 1859. Charities, £33. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
